{
  "answer": "In the poem \"Larkiyan parh rahi hain angrezi,\" Allama Iqbal observes—satirically—that girls learning English marks the moment when \"the nation has found the path to salvation,\" as Western style becomes the ideal while Eastern customs are condemned as sinful. He questions what dramatic outcome this cultural shift will produce.[^1]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, \"Larkiyan parh rahi hain angrezi\" [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/27-larkiyan-parh-rahi-hain-angrezi/translation/#p-289582).",
